query:
UPDATE musicians SET roleEn='Sitar & Compositions', bioEn='Deeply rooted in the Maihar and Rampur Gharanas, Hindol Deb is a preeminent sitarist and composer based in Cologne, Germany. Trained by Pandit Santosh Banerjee and Pandit Deepak Chaudhury (a disciple of Ravi Shankar), he earned a Master''s in Jazz Composition from the Hochschule für Musik Köln. His playing integrates the meditative Dhrupad Ang and the vocal-like Been Ang onto the sitar. Recipient of the National Sitar Scholarship and Sahitya Kala Parishad Fellowship.' WHERE id=1;
UPDATE musicians SET roleEn='Piano', bioEn='A master of sophisticated harmonic language ranging from classic counterpoint to atonality, Clemens Orth is Hindol''s long-time musical companion. With a New York jazz background, he uses external musical influences to set new accents in improvisations and to connect seemingly distant musical points. He has not only arranged many pieces on the album but shares Hindol''s artistic and philosophical convictions about cross-cultural musical dialogue.' WHERE id=2;
UPDATE musicians SET roleEn='Double Bass', bioEn='Christian Ramond studied at the University of Music in Cologne and received a scholarship from the Academy of Fine Arts in Banff, Canada. He has spent time in India, giving him a deep understanding of the music''s cultural roots. He has worked with jazz legends including Joe Pass, Albert Mangelsdorf, Kenny Wheeler, Lee Konitz, and Phillip Catherine, and has played in numerous television, radio and theater productions across many countries.' WHERE id=3;
UPDATE musicians SET nameEn='Jens Düppe & Christoph Hillmann', roleEn='Drums', bioEn='Jens Düppe is the drummer on the studio recording. Christoph Hillmann (b. 1964) joined the quartet for the India tour and live performances. A highly acclaimed musician who has played with national and international jazz greats for years, Hillmann is the winner of the New German Jazz Prize (2014) and has been involved in two ECHO-JAZZ award-winning productions. He is considered a particularly interactive player who elicits an unusually wide range of sounds and rhythms from the drums.' WHERE id=4;

